What is npm?
npm is a package manager. We use it in command to instal packages or third-party libraries in our project.

What is parcel/webpack?Why do we need it?
Parcel or webpack is a package. Which we install and execute in our project for adding additional features in our project.They bundle our all files along with thier dependecies into a single file.For Example parcel can do minification,image optimization, provide us with local server,compress our files and bundle them and much more.

What is .parcel-cache?
.parcel-cache stores information about project during development process.It analyze your code, dependencies and record them.So it dont re-analyze and re-parsing everytime from scratch each time you build.This help in improving speed.

What is npx?
npx is a command which we use to execute a package.

What is difference between dependencies vs devDependencies?
Dependencies section list the packages  required for project to function correctly.
devDependencies section list dependencies needed during developing project.

What is Tree Shaking?
Tree shaking is powerful optimization techinque.It removes unused or dead code from bundle and make bundle lean and efficient.

What is Hot Module Replacement?
It updates changes in your app without reloading complete webpage.

List down your favourite 5 superpowers of Parcel and describe any 3 of them in your
own words.
1-Image Optimization 
2-Local Server
3-Minification 
4-Tree Shaking
5-Compressing and Bundling

What is `.gitignore`? What should we add and not add into it?
.gitignore is a file which tells git which files or folders to ignore.

